{{outdated|Pantami Stadium has been built, and is now the home stadium of Gombe FC|date=September 2015}}
'''Abubakar Umar Memorial Stadium''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Gombe, Nigeria|Gombe]], [[Gombe State]], [[Nigeria]].  It has a capacity of 10,000 people, is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and it used to be the home stadium of [[Gombe United F.C.]]. The state government is planning on replacing it with a new [[Pantami Stadium|modern stadium]] that will cost 3 billion [[naira]]. [http://www.guardiannewsngr.com/sports/article15//indexn3_html?pdate=270908&ptitle=Gombe%20Earmarks%20N3%20Billion%20For%20New%20Stadium&cpdate=270908]

