{{infobox country at games |location[[Ashgabat]] |NOC=ASA |NOCname=American Samoa National Olympic Committee |games=Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games |year=2017 |date=17–27 September |flagcaption= |oldcode= |website={{url|}} |competitors=7 |sports=2 |flagbearer= |rank= |gold=0 |silver=0 |bronze=0 |officials= |appearances= |seealso=|}}
'''[[American Samoa]]''' competed at the [[2017 Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games]] held in [[Ashgabat]], [[Turkmenistan]] from September 17 to 27. 7 athletes represented American Samoa in 2 different sports during the event.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ashgabat2017.com/results/asa|title=American Samoa {{!}} The 5th Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games - 2017|last=|first=|date=|website=ashgabat2017.com|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref>
American Samoa made its debut in an [[Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games]] event along with other [[Oceania]] nations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ocasia.org/Game/GameParticular.aspx?9QoyD9QEWPdkzAjI/K7uyA==|title=Olympic Council of Asia : Games|website=www.ocasia.org|access-date=2017-10-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171212124624/http://www.ocasia.org/Game/GameParticular.aspx?9QoyD9QEWPdkzAjI%2FK7uyA=%3D|archive-date=2017-12-12|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.samoanews.com/2017-5th-asian-indoor-martial-arts-games-opening-ceremony|title=2017 5th Asian Indoor & Martial Arts Games Opening Ceremony {{!}} Samoa News|website=www.samoanews.com|language=en|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref>
