{{Infobox sport governing body |name = Brazilian Athletics Confederation |abbrev = CBAt |logo = Confederação Brasileira de Atletismo Logo.jpg |logosize = |sport = [[Athletics (sport)|Athletics]] |category = |image = |caption = |jurisdiction = Confederation |founded = {{Start date|1977|12|02}} |aff = [[IAAF]] |affdate = |region = [[CONSUDATLE]] |regionyear = {{Start date|1922}} |headquarters = [[São Paulo]], [[São Paulo (state)|São Paulo]] |location = |president = [[José Antonio Martins Fernandes]] |chairman = |chairperson = |chair = |chiefexec = |vicepresident = [[Warlindo Carneiro da Silva Filho]] |secretary = [[Martinho Nobre dos Santos]] |coach = |womenscoach = |key staff = |operating income = |sponsor = [[Caixa Econômica Federal]] |year closed = |replaced = Federação Brasileira de Sportes Atleticos |prevfounded = {{Start date|1914}} |url = www.cbat.org.br |countryflag = Brazil |countryflag2 = |countryflag3 = }}
The '''Brazilian Athletics Confederation''' ('''CBAt'''; ''Confederação Brasileira de Atletismo'') is the governing body for the sport of athletics in [[Brazil]].<ref name=cbat_1> {{ Citation | last = | first = | date = February 10, 2012 | title = Estatuto - Aprovado em 10.02.2012 | url = http://www.cbat.org.br/acbat/estatuto.pdf | publisher = Confederação Brasileira de Atletismo | page = | language = Portuguese | accessdate = September 26, 2012 }} </ref> President for the period 2013-2016 is [[José Antonio Martins Fernandes]].<ref name=lance_1> {{ Citation |last= |first= |date=February 10, 2012 |title=Toninho é eleito presidente da CBAt de 2013 a 2016 - Em assembleia realizada nesta sexta-feira, José Antonio Martins Fernandes recebeu 40 dos 41 votos |url=http://www.lancenet.com.br/minuto/Toninho-eleito-presidente-CBAt_0_643735719.html |publisher=[[Lance!]] |page= |language=Portuguese |accessdate=January 6, 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201150106/http://www.lancenet.com.br/minuto/Toninho-eleito-presidente-CBAt_0_643735719.html |archivedate=February 1, 2014 |df= }} </ref><ref name=cbat_1/><ref name=cbat_2> {{ Citation | last = | first = | date = February 2, 2011 | title = DIRETORIA - Período 2009 / 2012 - Atualizada em 02.02.11 | url = http://www.cbat.org.br/acbat/diretoria.pdf | publisher = Confederação Brasileira de Atletismo | page = | language = Portuguese | accessdate = September 26, 2012 }} </ref><ref name=iaaf_1> {{ Citation | last = | first = | date = | title = Confederação Brasileira de Atletismo | url = http://www.iaaf.org/about-iaaf/structure/member-federations/south-america#BRA | publisher = [[IAAF]] | page = | language = | accessdate = January 6, 2013 }} </ref>
== History == CBAt was founded on December 2, 1977. It replaced the Federação Brasileira de Sportes Atleticos, which was founded in 1914.<ref> {{ Citation | last = Matthews | first = Peter | date = | title = Historical Dictionary of Track and Field | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=kh97OBEUTn4C&pg=PA42&lpg=PA42&dq=history+Confedera%C3%A7%C3%A3o+Brasileira+de+Atletismo&source=bl&ots=Tl3WeYR0Ic&sig=U9BcaxIQ7IpuNrZF9FBVuTirzvA&hl=en&sa=X&ei=SA5jUMvkB-SN4gTDm4DYDw&sqi=2&ved=0CE0Q6AEwCQ#v=onepage&q&f=false | publisher = | page = 42 | language = | accessdate = September 26, 2012 }} </ref>
Former president until 2013 was [[Roberto Gesta de Melo]].
== Affiliations == CBAt is the national member federation for Brazil in the following international organisations: *[[IAAF|International Association of Athletics Federations]] (IAAF) *[[CONSUDATLE|Confederación Sudamericana de Atletismo]] (CONSUDATLE; ''South American Athletics Confederation'') *[[Association of Panamerican Athletics]] (APA) *[[Asociación Iberoamericana de Atletismo]] (AIA; ''Ibero-American Athletics Association'') Moreover, it is part of the following national organisations: *[[Brazilian Olympic Committee]]
== Member federations == {{Brazil Labelled Map}} CBAt comprises the athletics federations of the [[States of Brazil|Brazilian federal states]].<ref name=cbat_3> {{ Citation | last = | first = | date = | title = Federações | url = http://www.cbat.org.br/federacoes/default.asp | publisher = Confederação Brasileira de Atletismo | page = | language = Portuguese | accessdate = September 26, 2012 }} </ref> {| class=wikitable !State !Organisation !Link |- |[[Image:Bandeira do Acre.svg|30px|border]] [[Acre (state)|Acre]] |Federação Acreana de Atletismo - FAcA | |- |[[Image:Bandeira de Alagoas.svg|30px|border]] [[Alagoas]] |Federação Alagoana de Atletismo - FAAt | |- |[[Image:Bandeira do Amapá.svg|30px|border]] [[Amapá]] |Federação de Atletismo do Amapá - FAAp | |- |[[Image:Bandeira do Amazonas.svg|30px|border]] [[Amazonas (Brazilian state)|Amazonas]] |Federação Desportiva de Atletismo do Estado do Amazonas - FEDAEAM | |- |[[Image:Bandeira da Bahia.svg|30px|border]] [[Bahia]] |Federação Bahiana de Atletismo - FBA |[http://www.fba.org.br www.fba.org.br] |- |[[Image:Bandeira Estado Ceara Brasil.svg|30px|border]] [[Ceará]] |Federação Cearense de Atletismo - FCAt |[http://www.fcatletismo.com.br www.fcatletismo.com.br] |- |[[Image:Bandeira do Distrito Federal.svg|30px|border]] [[Federal District (Brazil)|Distrito Federal]] |Federação de Atletismo do Distrito Federal - FAtDF |[https://web.archive.org/web/20120115041058/http://fatdf.org.br/ www.fatdf.org.br] |- |[[Image:Bandeira do Espírito Santo.svg|30px|border]] [[Espírito Santo]] |Federação Capixaba de Atletismo - FECAt | |- |[[Image:Flag of Goiás.svg|30px|border]] [[Goiás]] |Federação Goiana de Atletismo - FGAt |[https://web.archive.org/web/20120923062856/http://atletismodegoias.com/ atletismodegoias.com] |- |[[Image:Bandeira do Maranhão.svg|30px|border]] [[Maranhão]] |Federação Atlética Maranhense - FAMA | |- |[[Image:Bandeira de Mato Grosso.svg|30px|border]] [[Mato Grosso]] |Federação de Atletismo de Mato Grosso - FAMT |[http