{{use dmy dates|date=July 2014}} {{infobox country at games | NOC = GUY | NOCname = Guyana Olympic Association | games = Summer Olympics | year = 1948 | flagcaption = Flag of [[British Guiana]] | oldcode = | website = | location = [[London]] | competitors = 4 | sports = 3 | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
'''[[British Guiana]]''' (now [[Guyana]]) competed at the '''[[1948 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[London]], England. Four competitors, all men, took part in seven events in three sports.<ref name="sports-reference">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/GUY/summer/1948/ |title=Guyana at the 1948 London Summer Games |accessdate=17 July 2014 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref> It was the first time that the nation competed at the Olympic Games.
==Athletics== {{main|Athletics at the 1948 Summer Olympics}}
==Cycling== {{main|Cycling at the 1948 Summer Olympics}} One cyclist represented British Guiana in 1948.
;[[Cycling at the 1948 Summer Olympics – Men's individual road race|Individual road race]] * [[Laddie Lewis]]
;[[Cycling at the 1948 Summer Olympics – Men's sprint|Sprint]] * [[Laddie Lewis]]
;[[Cycling at the 1948 Summer Olympics – Men's 1000m time trial|Time trial]] * [[Laddie Lewis]]
