{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Lincoln Road Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = Enfield Cricket Club - geograph.org.uk - 29383.jpg | location = [[Enfield, London|Enfield]], [[London]] | establishment = 1940 <small>(first recorded match)</small> | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1982 | club1 = [[Middlesex County Cricket Club|Middlesex]] | date = 2 September | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/468.html Ground profile }}
'''Lincoln Road Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Enfield, London|Enfield]], [[London]] (formerly [[Middlesex]]). The first recorded match on the ground was in 1940, when Enfield played a British Empire XI.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/468_misc.html Other matches played on Lincoln Road Ground]</ref>
Throughout its history, the ground has played host to a total of 39 Second XI fixtures for the [[Middlesex County Cricket Club|Middlesex Second XI]] in the [[Minor Counties Championship]], [[Second XI Championship]] and Second XI Trophy.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/468_minc.html Minor Counties Championship Matches played on Lincoln Road Ground]</ref><ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/468_sec.html Second XI Championship Matches played on Lincoln Road Ground]</ref><ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/468_set.html Second XI Trophy Matches played on Lincoln Road]</ref>
In 1982, the ground held its only [[List-A cricket|List-A]] match when [[Middlesex County Cricket Club|Middlesex]] played [[Cheshire County Cricket Club|Cheshire]] in the [[1982 NatWest Trophy]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/468_a.html List-A Matches played on Lincoln Road Ground]</ref>
In local domestic cricket, the ground is the home venue of Enfield Cricket Club.<ref>[http://enfield.play-cricket.com/home/home.asp Enfield Cricket Club] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715092700/http://enfield.play-cricket.com/home/home.asp |date=2011-07-15 }}</ref>
