{{Infobox football biography |name = Nabuaka Itimaroroa |image = |fullname = |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1976|09|30|df=y}} |birth_place = |height = {{height|m=}} |position = [[Midfielder]] |currentclub = |clubnumber = |youthyears1 = |youthclubs1 = |years1 = |clubs1 = |caps1 = |goals1 = |nationalyears1 = 2003 |nationalteam1 = [[Kiribati national football team|Kiribati]] |nationalcaps1 = 4 |nationalgoals1 = 0 }}
'''Nabuaka Itimaroroa''' (born 30 September 1976), is a retired [[Kiribati|I-Kiribati]] [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[midfielder]].
==International career== Itimaroroa represented Kiribati at the [[Men's football at the 2003 South Pacific Games|2003 Pacific Games]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/kiri-recintlp.html |title=Appearances and Goals for Kiribati National Team |accessdate=26 April 2018 |work=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]]}}</ref>
