{{Infobox football biography |name = Pieter Lehrer |image = |image_size = |caption = |fullname = Pieter Lehrer |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1965|1|29|df=y}} |birth_place = Antigua and Barbuda |death_date = |death_place = |height = |position = |currentclub = [[Harvard Crimson]] (Head coach) |youthyears1 = 1984–1985 |youthclubs1 = [[UCLA Bruins]] |years1 = |clubs1 = |caps1 = |goals1 = |manageryears1 = 2005–2012 |managerclubs1 = [[California Golden Bears]] (assistant) |manageryears2 = 2013– |managerclubs2 = [[Harvard Crimson]] }} '''Pieter Lehrer''', (born 29 January 1965) is a [[Canoe racing|sprint canoer]] from [[Antigua and Barbuda]] who competed in the mid-1990s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailycal.org/2012/09/10/the-fire-inside/|title=The fire inside: Pieter Lehrer's determination – The Daily Californian|work=The Daily Californian}}</ref> At the [[1996 Summer Olympics]], he advanced to the semifinals of the [[Canoeing at the 1996 Summer Olympics – Men's C-2 1000 metres|C-2 1000 m]] event, but did not compete. Lehrer is also the head coach for the [[Harvard Crimson men's soccer]] program.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pieter Lehrer|url=http://www.gocrimson.com/sports/msoc/coaches/lehrer_pieter|website=Harvard Athletics}}</ref>
