{{Infobox sport governing body | assocname= Russian Fencing Federation | abbrev = ФФР/FFR | logo= | logosize= | founded = 1992 | aff = [[International Fencing Federation]] | affdate = | region = [[European Fencing Confederation]] | regionyear = | image_border = | category = [[Fencing (sport)|Fencing]] | jurisdiction = Russia | headquarters = [[Moscow]] | president = Aleksandr Mikhailov | chairman = [[Alisher Usmanov]] | key staff = | chiefexec = | replaced = | url = http://www.rusfencing.ru/ | countryflag= Russia | countryflag2= }}
The '''Russian Fencing Federation''' ({{lang-ru|Федерация Фехтования России}}; {{lang-fr|Fédération d'escrime de la Russie}}) is the governing body for the sport of [[fencing (sport)|fencing]] in [[Russia]]. It was created proper in 1992, but its previous incarnation was affiliated to the [[Fédération Internationale d'Escrime]] in 1914.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Ottogalli |first1=Cécile |last2=Six |first2=Gérard |last3=Terret |first3=Thierry |date=2013 |title=L'Histoire de l'escrime. 1913–2013, un siècle de Fédération internationale d'escrime |location=Biarritz |publisher=Atlantica |isbn=978-2-7588-0485-7|page=38}}</ref> FFR is a member of the [[European Fencing Confederation]] and of the [[Russian Olympic Committee]]. It is composed of 35 regional organizations.
